<h3>What This Is</h3>
<p>
    The runnable <strong>trigger-detection engine</strong> ratified in
    <a href="/backlog/591-candidate-standard-mention-trigger-character-inline-picker/">#591</a>: an editable region
    that watches for a boundary-anchored <strong>trigger character</strong> (<code>@</code> people, <code>:</code>
    emoji, <code>#</code> reference, <code>/</code> command), slices the query that follows, anchors a popover to the
    <strong>caret</strong>, and routes results through a listbox. The same engine with a different trigger char and
    result set is every <code>@</code>-mention, <code>:</code>-emoji
    (<a href="/backlog/592-in-editor-inline-tooltip-emoji-picker-trigger/">#592</a>), <code>/</code>-command and
    <code>#</code>-reference field. It pairs with the <a href="/intents/inline-trigger/">Inline Trigger intent</a>
    (the declarative dimensions) and composes the <a href="/blocks/picker-surface/">Picker Surface</a> /
    <a href="/blocks/autocomplete/">Autocomplete</a> for results — it reinvents none of them.
</p>

<h3>Detection-only — the load-bearing scope (Fork 2-A)</h3>
<p>
    The block emits the <strong>resolved selection</strong> <code>{ key, query, range, item }</code> and
    <strong>stops</strong>; the consumer commits it. It owns no document model — the GitHub
    <code>&lt;text-expander&gt;</code> stance (<code>text-expander-value</code> hands you the replacement), not the
    ProseMirror <code>Suggestion.command</code> stance (which couples insertion into the editor doc). This is what
    lets one engine work uniformly in <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code> and
    <code>contenteditable</code>, and <strong>compose</strong> the rich-text standard
    (<a href="/backlog/590-candidate-standard-rich-text-contenteditable-editing/">#590</a>) for token insertion
    <em>without being blocked on it</em>. The block ships two reference insertion adapters — <code>text</code>
    (default; replaces the query range with a string) and <code>token</code> (composes #590's atom/token insertion)
    — but owns neither commit; the items-source and the committer are consumer-supplied behaviors.
</p>

<h3>Anatomy — the pipeline this block owns</h3>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Detect</strong> — on input, test for a trigger char at a valid boundary (per the intent's
        <code>boundaryPolicy</code>); detection <strong>suspends during IME composition</strong> (a forced
        invariant — composing <code>:</code> in a CJK IME must not fire the picker).</li>
    <li><strong>Slice</strong> — extract the query text from the trigger to the caret, bounded by the intent's
        <code>queryPolicy</code> (<code>minQueryLength</code> / <code>maxLength</code> / <code>allowSpaces</code>).</li>
    <li><strong>Anchor</strong> — tether the popover to the caret, a <em>virtual element</em> (not a stable DOM
        node), composing the <a href="/intents/anchor/">Anchor intent</a> over a caret rect: in
        <code>contenteditable</code> the DOM <code>Range.getBoundingClientRect()</code>; in
        <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code> a mirror-div caret measurement. Collision handling
        (flip/shift near the viewport edge) is load-bearing.</li>
    <li><strong>Route</strong> — render results through the <a href="/blocks/picker-surface/">picker surface</a> /
        autocomplete listbox; on selection, emit the resolved <code>{ key, query, range, item }</code> and return.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Accessibility — the APG editable combobox, verbatim (forced invariant)</h3>
<p>
    <strong>Virtual focus:</strong> DOM focus stays on the editable region; the listbox is navigated via
    <code>aria-activedescendant</code> with the active option scrolled into view by JS (browsers do not manage
    visibility for <code>aria-activedescendant</code>). The textbox carries <code>aria-expanded</code> /
    <code>aria-controls</code> / <code>aria-autocomplete</code>. A roving <code>tabindex</code> would steal focus
    from the text and is broken — this matches the WAI-ARIA APG
    <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/combobox/examples/combobox-autocomplete-list/">editable
    combobox with list autocomplete</a>; there is no dedicated &ldquo;mention&rdquo; pattern. Match counts announce
    through <a href="/intents/live-region-status/">live-region-status</a>. The native-first baseline degrades to a
    plain textbox with no inline suggestions.
</p>

<h3>Not a protocol</h3>
<p>
    A deterministic transform (trigger&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;query&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;anchor&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;route) with no
    swappable-vendor interop story — making it a protocol would be lock-in for no gain. The declarative axes (trigger
    set, boundary policy, query policy, insertion mode) live in the <a href="/intents/inline-trigger/">intent</a>;
    everything is supported by default with most-permissive defaults (open trigger registry, any-prefix boundary,
    no min query length), the restriction being the author's opt-in.
</p>

